node.text:
@wibmerfabio gives us a rundown on his Canyon Spectral:ON at our first CLLCTV Sessions event in Saalbach, Austria.
•
The Spectral ON features the new Shimano EP8 motor, providing more torque packed in a smaller and lighter package, making the frame design sleek and lighter than its previous iteration. Not only is it more powerful, but with a new 630Wh battery, the Spectral:ON will go further for longer.
•
During Fabios recovery from his foot injury, the Spectral:ON has been his go-to bike, allowing him to keep the legs spinning and get out on some chilled trail ride, but it will be one of his favourite go-to bikes post-injury as the speed in which he can session his local bikepark is too good to turn down.

Whilst at Crankworx Innsbruck, @tahneeseagrave met up with local renowned street and trials rider @wibmerfabio and the pair hit the trails, taking their Canyon Sender’s down the jump lines of bikepark Innsbruck there were plenty of whoop’s, whips and wheelies, as well as a few sneaky no-handers. So sit back and enjoy this POV from two riders at the top of their game on the dry and dusty trails of Austria.
•

node.text:
Collaborating with a fresh new brand like @nineyard_ on a custom paint project was always destined to provide awesome results.
•
Taking a bike made for the biggest mountain terrain like the Sender AL, and blending the street style origins of Nineyard meant we had to get creative with the design. From incorporating a crackle painting process to exploring new colours and surface finishes- the final scheme looks ready to send anything- whether in the city or the Bikepark.
•
As for the components- Nineyard's founder is @wibmerfabio - so it was only right to use the same parts Fabio runs- @ohlinsmtb suspension, @continental_tire Tyres, @magura_bicycle brakes, @dtswiss wheels and finished with @sqlab components.
•
Head to @nineyard_ and find out how you can win this very unique Sender AL.
•
#MyCanyon #SenderAL #MTB #DownhillBike #Mountainbike

A unique limited-edition Ultimate CF SLX 8 LTD Erik Spiekermann - Our second Artist Edition bike that celebrates creative visionaries with a passion for cycling.
•
@espiekermann is a typographer and type designer, a passionate cyclist and bike collector. He’s designed countless well-known fonts as well as helping create corporate design programs for world-renowned companies. And now his latest project is here: the Ultimate CF SLX 8 LTD.
•
“In cycling the right measurements determine how good a bike feels and rides. And just like in bike design graphic design involves measurements too. They’re all connected. If I change one parameter I have to rethink all the other ones. Expressing the language of graphical design in the Ultimate’s artwork worked so well thanks to the frame’s clean pared-back lines.
•
I am fascinated by the graphic symbols we use to annotate sizes, lengths, diameters, and angles. Lines connect terminal points that are precisely defined by arrows. In light blue on a dark background, it looks like a secret code only understood by a select few.” - Erik Spiekermann.
•
Hit the link in bio to find out more about the Ultimate CF SLX 8 LTD.
•

Over 1000 kilometres and 14.325 metres of climbing through the Death Valley in only seven days.  No wonder they called this project @theimpossibleroute 
•
The @the_vegan_cyclist and @jeremiah_bishop_mtb_, together with @canyon_na, put together a special project across the Death Valley desert. From Yuma, Arizona, to Bishop, California; A route known by motorcyclists but never done before on a bicycle was taken to the test by these two cyclists and their Grail bikes.
•
Make sure to follow the episodes of this incredible adventure on our Youtube channel or watch the entire journey on the @the_vegan_cyclist Youtube channel.
•
#MyCanyon #theimpossibleroute #GrailCF #GravelBike #GravelRide #Bikepacking

Because he knows he has what it takes to cross the famous finish line at Alii Drive first and write his name into the history books as a Triathlon World Champion.

On a sunny day in March on the slopes of Folgaria, Italy, Italian @canyon_cllctv  ambassador @andrea_maranelli was undertaking his #PowerOnGameON challenge to see how many metres he could both climb and descend in one hour.
•
Taking the Torque:ON donned with spiked tyres, he began his ascent up the slopes, somewhat regretting his decision of not getting out earlier as the slopes had begun to soften under the blazing March sun.
•
Passing bewildered skiers, Andrea managed to rack up 15km, and a total of 1027metres of climbing and descending. For a power hour on the slopes, we think that’s pretty impressive!
•
#MyCanyon #CLLCTV #PowerONGameON #TorqueON #EMTB

node.text:
@wibmerfabio gives us a rundown on his Canyon Spectral:ON at our first CLLCTV Sessions event in Saalbach, Austria.
•
The Spectral ON features the new Shimano EP8 motor, providing more torque packed in a smaller and lighter package, making the frame design sleek and lighter than its previous iteration. Not only is it more powerful, but with a new 630Wh battery, the Spectral:ON will go further for longer.
•
During Fabios recovery from his foot injury, the Spectral:ON has been his go-to bike, allowing him to keep the legs spinning and get out on some chilled trail ride, but it will be one of his favourite go-to bikes post-injury as the speed in which he can session his local bikepark is too good to turn down.

node.text:
Speedmax follows the old adage of “does what it says on the tin.” So if you’re looking for fast speeds, and to push your capabilities to the max, then you may have just found your new road racing, triathlon smashing and time-trialling best friend.
•
Everything on the Speedmax has been designed to be intuitive, taking feedback from our athletes and culminating in a rider-centric fitting system that ensures that there is a perfect setup for every rider. This 5 time Kona winning bike has also been designed in collaboration with F1 aerodynamic experts Swiss Side, making it faster than its previous iterations and adding to its reputation of being a pure speed machine.
•
#MyCanyon #Speedmax
•
📸 @maddogboris

180 km in 3.55.26. We’re still getting our heads around how those numbers are possible, yet  that's exactly what Jan Frodeno cranked out on the Speedmax CFR on his way to smashing his own world record at the @tri.battle. 

This was Jan’s first long-distance triathlon aboard the Speedmax CFR. To help both him and Lionel Sanders achieve the fastest bike splits possible, our engineers have been working hard on new prototype cockpits, which Jan chose to put to the test during the event. 

The striking Mono Stick design allows Jan to wrap his hands around the bar ends and reduce his frontal surface area even further, increasing aerodynamic performance. These gains are reserved to our pro athletes for now, but we look forward to offering the Mono Stick design to Speedmax CFR and CF SLX customers in the near future. Want to ride with the same setup as the world record breaker. This is how.

Find the whole story of the tri.battle in the linkinbio!

📸 @pohlmann_photo

node.text:
After the dust has settled, after the last drop of Champagne has flowed, it’s time to look back on three weeks of highs at the 2021 Tour de France.

When was the last time a wildcard team crashed the party at the world’s biggest bike race quite like @alpecinfenix did? The emotion of @mathieuvanderpoel’s win on Stage 2, and with it finally the Maillot Jaune that had forever evaded his grandfather, the ecstasy the next day as Tim Merlier sprinted to victory to bring up the double. MVDP’s attacking display and dogged defense of the Yellow Jersey was a highlight of week one, while Jasper Philipsen carried the baton as the closest sprint rival to Mark Cavendish.

@movistar_team continued a run of consistently placing a rider in the top-10 overall thanks to the efforts of @enric_mas_ who finished 6th in Paris, while @alejandvalverde rolled back the years with a 2nd place at one of the race’s hardest summit finishes to Andorra.

Elsewhere @arkeasamsic rode strongly for @nairoquincoficial’s assault on the Mountains Classification. Although ultimately coming up short, the Colombian wore the iconic Polka Dot Jersey for four stages as the Tour crossed some of its iconic summits.

With the curtain now fallen on 21 days of action, we look ahead to the Vuelta a España for our next Grand Tour fix just a few weeks away. ¡Vamos!

Make sure to check out the Tour de France 2021 race wrap-up in our blog in the linkinbio!

#MyCanyon 

📸 @pohlmann_photo & @kramon_velophoto
